news.title: CAG's proposal to charge higher land premium ignored by Ahmedabad civic body
news.para: The CAG had audited 13 slum redevelopment schemes and found that the land premium was fixed without considering the formula agreed under "land disposable policy of the state government".

news.title: Rush to beat jantri deadline spurs 57% rise in revenue in Gujarat
news.para: The number of properties registered increased from 4,36,665 in Jan-March 2022 to 5,15,116 in the same period this year- a rise of 18%. The four major cities of Ahmedabad, Surat, Vadodara and Rajkot accounted for 60% to 70% of all the properties registered in the state.

news.title: DDA sets December 2023 deadline for Delhi's Kathputli Colony
news.para: After the construction work is completed, a computerised draw of lots will be done and DDA will send a demand letter to the allottees asking them to submit Rs 1.25 lakh as symbolic amount.

news.title: Maharashtra government set to buy Air India's building for Rs 1,600 crore
news.para: Deputy chief minister Devendra Fadnavis said, “If we get the building, we can save the rent the state government is paying right now. Several state offices are housed in private spaces across south Mumbai and is costing a huge sum every month. ”

news.title: Piramal Capital sells two offices in Mumbai's BKC to TCG Urban Infra for Rs 110 crore
news.para: This is part of a buyback deal as TCG Urban Infrastructure had sold the same office space, in 2013, to Dewan Housing Finance Corporation Ltd (DHFL), which has now merged with Piramal Capital & Housing Finance Ltd.

news.title: After long wait, work begins to complete Jaypee Wish Town towers
news.para: Since the five-member Implementation and Monitoring Committee (IMC) was set up last month, the Mumbai-based group has moved on speeding up construction in 62 towers, in addition to 15 where work is not taking place.

news.title: Naredco urges Uttar Pradesh government to bring scheme for builders to clear land dues of authorities
news.para: ​Naredco-UP President R K Arora met Manoj Kumar Singh, Infrastructure & Industrial Development Commissioner, UP Government on Monday to raise the issue of pending land dues and urge him to adopt a settlement policy similar to the 'Vivad se Viswas' scheme by the Centre and the 'Samadhan Se Vikas' scheme of Haryana.

news.title: Noida authority hires agency to keep tabs on Sports City's status
news.para: CEO Ritu Maheshwari said, "We have hired an agency which will assist us in planning, gap identification and remedies need for completing the sports facilities at the project site."

news.title: Circle rates increased in Gurugram's main housing hubs
news.para: After the revision, the circle rates in sectors adjoining the Southern Peripheral Road (SPR), Golf Course Road and Dwarka Expressway - areas where real estate has seen a boom - have increased by up to 30%.

news.title: Jaipur development body demolishes four Sanganer colonies
news.para: The JDA team first demolished an upcoming colony on a land measuring around 4 bigha in Shyampura Buhariya village. The second colony that was destroyed was coming up in Mohanpura villages on around 2 bighas.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body extends deadline for gunthewari formalisation
news.para: This will be the last chance for the owners of the constructions to get their properties legal or there will be a risk of the properties being unless the government comes up with another round of regularisation.

news.title: Residents of Hubballi, Dharwad can pay property tax from cellphone now
news.para: It is now the era of technology and almost all financial transactions are taking place electronically. Now Hubballi-Dharwad Municipal Corporation has taken steps to facilitate citizens to pay their property tax while sitting at home, using a mobile phone.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to organise property tax grievance redress camp on April 18
news.para: ​​The citizens who have complaints related to property tax can visit the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation’s zonal offices from 10.30am to 2pm and from 3pm to 5pm.

news.title: Nashik civic chief instructs officials to ensure inclusion of all NMC properties in land records
news.para: Pulkundwar’s instructions come in wake of a written question that BJP MLA from Nashik East Rahul Dikhle raised during the recent Budget session of the assembly.

news.title: Gurugram development body plans 1% fee on property transfers to fund SPR's revamp
news.para: The Gurugram Metropolitan Development Authority is planning to impose a 1% duty on transfer of immovable properties located along the 14km stretch of the Southern Peripheral Road from Ghata village to NH-8 near Kherki Daula for the next three years.
